Sentencas: To expand the processing options for low-temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs), the hybridization of powder processing and vacuum deposition is attempted.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability

Sentencas: Nanostructured nickel-yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) anode functional layer (AFL) and YSZ/gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) bi-layer electrolyte are fabricated over a sintered anode support by pulsed laser deposition (PLD), a physical vapor deposition technology.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability

Sentencas: The most common powder-processed (screen-printed and sintered) La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95(LSCF-GDC) composite cathode is applied over vacuum-deposited thin-film components.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability

Sentencas: When LSCF-GDC is sintered at a general sintering temperature of 1050 degrees C then the continuity of the GDC buffer is lost and excessive interdiffusion between the cathode and the electrolyte has occurred at the interface.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability

Sentencas: On the other hand, if the sintering temperature is lowered to 950 degrees C, peak power density more than 1.7 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees C is obtained.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability

Sentencas: Moreover, the operation stability of the hybrid SOFC (degradation rate similar to 8%/000 h) is superior to that of the SOFC with a vacuum-processed nanostructure cathode (degradation rate similar to 21%/100 h) when exposed to 0.7 A cm(-2) at 650 degrees C, which is a significantly harsh degradation test condition for LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Sintered powder-base cathode over vacuum-deposited thin-film electrolyte of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell: Performance and stability
